### ShineHub VPP Batch Event Dispatch API Console
# This file can be run directly inside VS Code if you install the "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client).
# It allows you to test and explore all VPP event scheduling and simulation flows manually.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000
@batchId = {{createEvent.response.body.batch.id}}
@commandId = cmd-sample-placeholder

### 1. Check API Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. List Fleet Devices
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/devices
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. List Saved Fleet Groups
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/groups
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Validate Event Configuration
# Evaluates safety rules, target selector counts, and overlapping schedules (conflicts).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/validate
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "targetSelector": {
    "region": "NSW"
  },
  "type": "discharge",
  "powerKw": 5,
  "startAt": "2026-07-10T12:00:00.000Z",
  "durationMinutes": 30
}

###

### 5. Create Event & Batch
# If validation passes, this creates the VPP Event, its associated Dispatch Batch, 
# and pending Commands for all matched target devices.
# @name createEvent
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "targetSelector": {
    "region": "NSW"
  },
  "type": "discharge",
  "powerKw": 5,
  "startAt": "2026-07-10T12:00:00.000Z",
  "durationMinutes": 30,
  "createdBy": "ops.lead@shinehub.local"
}

###

### 6. Dispatch Batch Commands
# Triggers command execution by starting the asynchronous MQTT simulation.
# (This utilizes the ID captured from the createEvent response above).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/batches/{{batchId}}/dispatch
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. Get Batch Details
# Fetches summary counts and status for a specific dispatch batch.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/batches/{{batchId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 8. List Batch Commands
# Retrieves status details and retry counts for all commands in this batch.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/batches/{{batchId}}/commands
Accept: application/json

###

### 9. Get Batch Audit Log
# Returns the audit trails for this batch and all related command transitions.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/batches/{{batchId}}/audit
Accept: application/json

###

### 10. Manual Mock Telemetry Ingestion
# Allows you to force state updates (e.g. mock success/failure callbacks) on a specific command.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/telemetry
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "commandId": "cmd-sample-placeholder",
  "status": "executed",
  "reason": "Manually simulated success telemetry callback."
}

###

### 11. Retry Failed Command
# Retries a command that failed execution, failed to publish, or timed out.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/commands/{{commandId}}/retry
Accept: application/json

###

### 12. Run Crash Recovery worker
# Scans and requeues any commands stuck in transitioning states.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/recovery/run
Accept: application/json
